    <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
    <section class="sw-section">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p>
          Every religion has a class of men who interpret the unseen for the masses — men who are not to be questioned, whose images and declarations are accepted on faith alone. The ancient world had the priests of Ra and Baal. The modern world has NASA.
        </p>
        <p>
          Lab coats replaced robes, composite images replaced idols, and the congregation moved from the temple to the classroom — but the function is identical. The people are told what the universe looks like by a small group of men they will never meet, using instruments they will never see, producing images they did not take.
        </p>
        <p>
          This page examines how the space establishment operates as a religious institution, demanding faith in what no common man has ever independently verified.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── ACCORDION SECTIONS ── -->
    <section class="sw-accordion-section">
      <p class="sw-accordion-label">&#8213; The Dark Foundations &#8213;</p>
      <h2 class="sw-accordion-title">A Detailed Historical Report</h2>
      <p class="sw-accordion-sub">Select any section to expand it.</p>

      <div class="sw-accordion">

        <!-- INTRODUCTION -->
        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Introduction</span><span class="sw-part-title">The Hidden Foundation of NASA</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>The story of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) is one of the most celebrated narratives in modern history. The tale of American ingenuity conquering the heavens, putting men on the moon, and pushing the boundaries of human exploration has been told countless times. But beneath the polished veneer of patriotic achievement lies a far darker foundation — one built upon the expertise of Nazi war criminals, the rituals of self-proclaimed occultists, and the deep involvement of secret societies.</p>
            <p>This report examines the well-documented historical record surrounding three key areas: First, Operation Paperclip, the covert U.S. intelligence program that brought over 1,600 German scientists — many of them members of the Nazi Party and the SS — to America after World War II. Second, the foundational role of Jack Parsons, a devoted follower of Aleister Crowley and a self-proclaimed Antichrist, in establishing the Jet Propulsion Laboratory (JPL). Third, the pervasive presence of Freemasonry among NASA's leadership and astronaut corps, and the occult symbolism woven throughout its missions.</p>
            <p>As those who follow Yahushua the Messiah and walk in the Torah, we are called to test all things and hold fast to what is good (1 Thessalonians 5:21). The Scriptures warn us that the adversary presents himself as an angel of light (2 Corinthians 11:14), and that the rulers of this present darkness operate through principalities and powers that most people never perceive. What you will read in this report is not conspiracy theory — it is documented, verifiable history.</p>
            <div class="sw-scripture-block">
              <p class="sw-scripture-label">&#9656; Scripture</p>
              <p>"For we wrestle not against flesh and blood, but against principalities, against powers, against the rulers of the darkness of this world, against spiritual wickedness in high places." — <strong>Ephesians 6:12</strong></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- PART I -->
        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Part I</span><span class="sw-part-title">Operation Paperclip — Nazis at the Heart of NASA</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">The Program That Brought Nazis to America</h3>
            <p>In the spring of 1945, as Allied forces closed in on Nazi Germany, American military and intelligence officials launched a covert operation originally codenamed "Operation Overcast," later renamed "Operation Paperclip." The name reportedly came from the paperclips used to mark the files of scientists with particularly problematic Nazi backgrounds.</p>
            <p>Between 1945 and 1990, Operation Paperclip imported approximately 1,600 German scientists, engineers, and technicians to the United States. President Harry Truman authorized the program with one stipulation: no one who had been "a member of the Nazi Party, and more than a nominal participant in its activities" was to be admitted. In practice, the Joint Intelligence Objectives Agency (JIOA) routinely altered, sanitized, or outright fabricated background files to make Nazi war criminals appear eligible.</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">Wernher von Braun — The Nazi Father of NASA</h3>
            <p>No figure better embodies the moral compromise at the heart of NASA than Wernher von Braun. German documents show he applied for membership in the Nazi Party on November 12, 1937. He joined the SS on November 1, 1933, and by 1943 had risen to the rank of SS-Sturmbannführer (Major). Photographs exist of von Braun proudly wearing his SS uniform alongside Heinrich Himmler himself.</p>
            <p>As technical director of the Peenemünde Army Research Center, von Braun oversaw the V-2 ballistic missile, which killed approximately 5,000 civilians. Far more disturbing, as many as 20,000 concentration camp prisoners died assembling the weapons at the underground Mittelwerk factory. Von Braun personally visited the facility at least a dozen times and is documented to have visited Buchenwald concentration camp to handpick inmates for slave labor.</p>
            <p>Yet this man was brought to America, given a new identity, and placed at the very heart of the U.S. space program. He became the first director of NASA's Marshall Space Flight Center in 1960 and was the chief architect of the Saturn V rocket. Walt Disney featured him on national television in 1955 as a wholesome American hero. His Nazi past was classified and concealed for decades.</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">Other Key Nazi Scientists in NASA</h3>
            <p><strong>Kurt Debus</strong> — a Nazi Party member and SS officer who became the first director of NASA's Kennedy Space Center, personally overseeing the Apollo 11 launch. A conference facility at Kennedy Space Center still bears his name.</p>
            <p><strong>Arthur Rudolph</strong> — classified by American officials as an "ardent Nazi," he personally oversaw slave labor at Mittelwerk where prisoners were executed. These facts were erased from his file. He managed teams working on the Saturn V rocket and later publicly stated, "I read Mein Kampf and agreed with a lot of things in it." He was forced to leave the U.S. in 1984 when confronted with evidence of his war crimes.</p>
            <p><strong>Hubertus Strughold</strong> — made major contributions to space medicine. He was inducted into the International Space Hall of Fame in 1978 but removed in 2006 when his wartime record came to fuller light, having been connected to horrific human experiments on concentration camp prisoners.</p>
            <p><strong>Georg Rickhey</strong> — managed the acquisition of enslaved workers at Mittelwerk and was extradited to West Germany on war crimes charges.</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">The Nazi Occult Environment</h3>
            <p>The Nazi Party itself emerged from the <strong>Thule Society</strong>, a German occultist group whose membership included Rudolf Hess, Alfred Rosenberg, and Dietrich Eckart — who personally mentored Hitler and to whom Mein Kampf was dedicated.</p>
            <p>Himmler, under whom von Braun served as an SS officer, founded the <strong>Ahnenerbe</strong> ("Ancestral Heritage") in 1935 — a pseudoscientific SS organization devoted to searching for supposed Aryan origins. The SS itself was organized along quasi-mystical, neo-pagan lines, with runic symbols, initiation rituals, and deliberate blurring of the line between science and metaphysics. When America imported these men, it imported not merely their technical expertise, but the spiritual atmosphere in which that expertise had been cultivated.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- PART II -->
        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Part II</span><span class="sw-part-title">Jack Parsons — The Occultist Who Founded JPL</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">The Father of American Rocketry</h3>
            <p>John Whiteside "Jack" Parsons (1914–1952) co-founded the Jet Propulsion Laboratory (JPL), which remains one of NASA's most critical facilities for space exploration. He co-founded Aerojet, one of the first American rocket companies. He pioneered the development of solid rocket fuel — versions of which were later used by NASA. A crater on the dark side of the moon is named after him.</p>
            <p>But Jack Parsons was also a devoted follower of Aleister Crowley — the man who called himself "The Great Beast 666." Parsons was a high priest in Crowley's occult order, a practitioner of sex magic rituals, and a self-proclaimed Antichrist. Among aerospace insiders, JPL was nicknamed "Jack Parsons' Laboratory."</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">Conversion to Thelema</h3>
            <p>In January 1939, Parsons was introduced to the Church of Thelema in Hollywood, where he witnessed the "Gnostic Mass" — a ritual devised by Crowley as a deliberate perversion of the Catholic Mass. He joined the Agape Lodge, the California branch of Crowley's Ordo Templi Orientis (O.T.O.), a quasi-Masonic organization practicing sexual magic. He gave almost all of his salary to support the O.T.O. and referred to Crowley as his "Most Beloved Father." He used his Pasadena mansion on "Millionaire's Row" as the Lodge's headquarters.</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">Occultism and Rocketry: Two Sides of One Coin</h3>
            <p>Parsons famously recited Crowley's poem "Hymn to Pan" as a good luck invocation before rocket tests. He performed ritual magic at his workplace and frequently invited colleagues to attend occult ceremonies. His co-workers described him performing these recitations in an ecstatic manner.</p>
            <p>The location of JPL itself, near Devil's Gate Dam in Pasadena, was reportedly selected by Parsons due to his belief that the location was a portal to Hell. The Jet Propulsion Laboratory was officially founded on <strong>October 31 — Halloween — in 1936.</strong></p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">The Babalon Working</h3>
            <p>In 1945–1946, Parsons performed a series of rituals known as the "Babalon Working" with none other than <strong>L. Ron Hubbard</strong>, the future founder of Scientology. The Babalon Working drew upon Enochian magic — a system some scholars believe was designed to set in motion the destructive forces of the Apocalypse.</p>
            <p>The stated purpose was breathtaking in its blasphemy: Parsons sought to invoke the Thelemic goddess "Babalon" — derived directly from the "Whore of Babylon" in Revelation 17 — and magically conceive a "Moonchild," a Thelemic anti-Messiah intended to overthrow the current spiritual order. Even Aleister Crowley was disturbed, writing: "Apparently Parsons or Hubbard or somebody is producing a Moonchild. I get fairly frantic when I contemplate the idiocy of these louts!"</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">The Self-Proclaimed Antichrist</h3>
            <p>After Hubbard betrayed Parsons — stealing his money and running off with his girlfriend — Parsons took a formal "Oath of the Antichrist," declaring himself to embody an entity named "Belarion Armillus Al Dajjal, the Antichrist," who had "come to fulfill the law of the Beast 666." He practiced black magic, witchcraft, and voodoo, and reported having out-of-body experiences in which he was transported to the biblical city of Chorazin — one of the cities cursed by Yahushua Himself (Matthew 11:21).</p>
            <p>Parsons died on June 17, 1952, in a mysterious explosion in his home laboratory. This is the man whose work helped establish the Jet Propulsion Laboratory — still operational today as NASA's primary center for robotic exploration of the solar system.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- PART III -->
        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Part III</span><span class="sw-part-title">Freemasonry and NASA</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">Masonic Leadership at NASA</h3>
            <p>The connections between Freemasonry and NASA are not speculation — they are openly acknowledged by the Masonic organizations themselves. Key figures include:</p>
            <p><strong>T. Keith Glennan</strong>, the first Administrator of NASA, was a Yale graduate and member of Skull and Bones.</p>
            <p><strong>James Edwin Webb</strong>, NASA's administrator from 1961 to 1968 — the critical Apollo years — was a known Freemason.</p>
            <p><strong>C. Fred Kleinknecht</strong>, who served as manager of the Apollo Program at NASA, later became the Sovereign Grand Commander of the 33rd Degree Supreme Council of the Ancient and Accepted Scottish Rite of Freemasonry — the highest position in Scottish Rite Freemasonry in the United States. He held this position for eighteen years.</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">Masonic Astronauts</h3>
            <p><strong>Edwin "Buzz" Aldrin Jr.</strong> — the second man to walk on the moon — was an active Freemason. According to the Scottish Rite's own records, the Grand Master of Texas approved his request to open a Representation of the Grand Lodge of Texas on the Moon. Aldrin carried a handmade silk Masonic flag to the lunar surface and later presented it at the House of the Temple in Washington, D.C. The November 1969 issue of The New Age Magazine (official Scottish Rite publication) declared: <em>"When man reaches new worlds, Masonry will be there!"</em></p>
            <p><strong>John Glenn Jr.</strong> — the first American to orbit the Earth — was made a "Mason at sight" by the Grand Master of Ohio and received the honorary 33° degree.</p>
            <p><strong>Leroy Gordon Cooper Jr.</strong> — Master Mason and 33° honorary degree recipient. <strong>Donn Eisele</strong> — Apollo 7, Freemason. <strong>Virgil "Gus" Grissom</strong> — Master Mason, who died in the Apollo 1 fire. <strong>Edgar Mitchell</strong> — Apollo 14, walked on the lunar surface, Freemason. <strong>James Irwin</strong> — Apollo 15, Freemason.</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">Apollo Mission Symbolism</h3>
            <p>The very name "Apollo" chosen for America's moon program is deeply significant. Apollo is not merely a figure from Greek mythology — in Scripture, the name appears in <strong>Revelation 9:11</strong> as "Apollyon," the angel of the bottomless pit, the Destroyer. The Hebrew equivalent is "Abaddon."</p>
            <p>Researchers have noted that the stylized "A" in the Apollo logo appears to incorporate the constellation Orion — which in Egyptian mythology represents Osiris, the god of the dead. According to analyses of the Apollo 11 landing, exactly <strong>thirty-three minutes</strong> after landing at the chosen site, Orion's Belt would have been perfectly aligned on the moon's horizon. The number 33 holds supreme significance in Freemasonry as the highest degree of the Scottish Rite.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- PART IV -->
        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Part IV</span><span class="sw-part-title">A Scriptural Perspective</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">The Tower of Babel Pattern</h3>
            <p>When we examine the origins of NASA through the lens of Scripture, a familiar pattern emerges. In Genesis 11:4, the people said, "Come, let us build us a city and a tower, whose top may reach unto heaven; and let us make us a name." The impulse to "reach unto heaven" — to ascend beyond the boundaries Yahuah has established — is as old as human rebellion itself. It is the same impulse described in Isaiah 14:13–14, where Lucifer declared: "I will ascend into heaven... I will be like the Most High."</p>
            <p>Jack Parsons explicitly understood his rocketry work in these terms. For him, rocketry freed the body from the bonds of Earth, while the occult freed the mind and soul. He saw both pursuits as part of the same spiritual project — the ascent of man beyond divine boundaries.</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">The Mixing of Clean and Unclean</h3>
            <p>The Torah teaches the fundamental principle of separation — between clean and unclean, holy and profane, light and darkness. In Leviticus 10:10, Yahuah commands: "And that ye may put difference between holy and unholy, and between unclean and clean." Operation Paperclip represents perhaps the most dramatic violation of this principle in modern history. Men who served the most systematically evil regime in human memory — who wore the SS uniform, who benefited from slave labor — were not merely tolerated but celebrated and placed in positions of national leadership.</p>
            <p><strong>2 Corinthians 6:14</strong> asks, "What fellowship hath righteousness with unrighteousness? And what communion hath light with darkness?" The answer, according to Scripture, is none. Yet the United States government deliberately chose to build its most prestigious scientific achievement upon this exact kind of unholy fellowship.</p>

            <h3 class="sw-body-heading">The Significance of Names and Symbols</h3>
            <p>In Hebrew thought, names carry profound spiritual significance. That the American space program was named after Apollo — the Destroyer of Revelation 9:11 — deserves serious reflection. That its most critical laboratory was founded by a self-proclaimed Antichrist who performed rituals invoking the Whore of Babylon is not a minor historical footnote. That its leadership and astronaut corps were heavily populated by members of a fraternal order whose rituals reach back to the mystery religions of ancient Egypt and Babylon speaks to the spiritual forces operating behind the scenes.</p>
            <p>Yahushua said, "By their fruits ye shall know them" (Matthew 7:20). When we examine the roots of NASA, we find Nazi war criminals, occultist rituals invoking anti-Messiah figures, and the pervasive presence of secret societies.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- CONCLUSION -->
        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Conclusion</span><span class="sw-part-title">Three Streams of Darkness</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>This report has documented three streams of darkness that converged to form the foundation of NASA and the American space program:</p>
            <p><strong>First,</strong> Operation Paperclip brought approximately 1,600 German scientists to America — many of them Nazi Party members, SS officers, and beneficiaries of concentration camp slave labor — and placed them in the most senior positions within the U.S. rocket and space programs. Their Nazi records were deliberately sanitized and concealed from the American public. These men operated within a Third Reich culture steeped in Teutonic mysticism and occult pseudo-science through organizations like Himmler's Ahnenerbe.</p>
            <p><strong>Second,</strong> Jack Parsons, one of the most important founding figures of American rocketry and the Jet Propulsion Laboratory, was a devoted disciple of Aleister Crowley, the head of an occult lodge, a practitioner of sex magic and Enochian rituals, and a self-proclaimed Antichrist who performed ceremonies explicitly designed to invoke the Whore of Babylon and birth an anti-Messiah figure. He saw no separation between his rocket science and his occultism — both were expressions of the same desire to transcend the boundaries of the physical world.</p>
            <p><strong>Third,</strong> Freemasonry has maintained a pervasive and openly acknowledged presence throughout NASA's history, from its earliest administrators to its most celebrated astronauts. Masonic flags were carried to the lunar surface. Masonic territorial jurisdiction was formally claimed on the moon. The symbolism of the Apollo program — bearing the name of the Destroyer from Revelation — reflects themes consistent with esoteric and Masonic tradition.</p>
            <p>None of this is hidden. It is all documented in mainstream historical sources, in Masonic publications, in NASA's own archives, and in the writings of the individuals involved. The question is not whether these things are true — the question is what they mean.</p>
            <div class="sw-scripture-block">
              <p class="sw-scripture-label">&#9656; Scripture</p>
              <p>"And have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove them." — <strong>Ephesians 5:11</strong></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

